article.headline: UTEP 74, Miss. Valley St. 58
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- John Tofi led four UTEP players in double figures with 19 points in a 74-58 victory against winless Mississippi Valley State in the Sun Bowl tournament Tuesday night. The Miners (7-2) will play either Georgetown or Colgate in Wednesday's tournament championship. UTEP took a 30-12 lead in the first 15 minutes and shot 55 percent in the first half. Their top three scorers -- Tofi, Edgar Moreno (14) and Jason Williams (13) -- combined to make 16 of 26 field goals. Kevin Henderson scored 11 points and was 3-of-4 on 3-pointers. Jesse Taylor of Mississippi Valley State (0-8) led all scorers with 20 points on 6-of-8 shooting. Mike Thomas had 10 points and 10 turnovers. Mississippi Valley State pulled within 62-54 with 3½ minutes left, but UTEP responded with an 11-2 run. Tofi led all rebounders with nine, and Moreno had a game-high five steals.
